Sentencas: CuCo2O4 spinel prepared via an EDTA-citric acid process was studied as a candidate solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) cathode material at intermediate temperatures (IT).
Titulo: Copper cobalt spinel as a high performance cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: CuCo2O4 cathodes were measured using thermal gravimetric analysis, X-ray diffraction and scanning electron microscopy.
Titulo: Copper cobalt spinel as a high performance cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: AC impedance spectroscopy and DC polarization measurements were used to study the electrode performance.
Titulo: Copper cobalt spinel as a high performance cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The obtained value of the polarization resistances at 800 degrees C was 0.12 Omega cm(2) with a maximum power density of 972 mW cm(-2).
Titulo: Copper cobalt spinel as a high performance cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
